    <para id="id6171931">The Fourier transform 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{X rSub { size 8{m} }  \( f \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is repeated at 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">±</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>c</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ +- f rSub { size 8{c} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</para>
    <para id="id3661897">2/ Demodulation (detection) of AM, suppressed carrier</para>
    <figure id="id3209310">
      <media id="id1172208997586" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics10-8cff.png" mime-type="image/png" height="104" width="264"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id4023206">The original signal 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{x rSub { size 8{m} }  \( t \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> can be recovered by modulating the modulated signal and passing the result through a lowpass filter, a process called demodulation or detection.</para>
    <figure id="id6181035">
      <media id="id1172204244831" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics11-7472.png" mime-type="image/png" height="183" width="527"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id4563127">3/ AM, suppressed carrier radio</para>
    <para id="id5431923">A radio communication system that consists of a transmitter and receiver and which uses suppressed carrier AM is shown below. </para>
