    <para id="id5373781">The spectrum of y(t) involves the spectrum of 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mtext>cos</m:mtext><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mn>2πf</m:mn><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>c</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msub><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"cos" rSup { size 8{2} }  \( 2πf rSub { size 8{c} } t \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> which can be found by the trigonometric identity or as shown below.</para>
